{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Bread","content":["Place 5 g sugar, 50  g flour, 50 g water and yeast in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>1 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Leave in mixing bowl, with lid on, to rest for 30 minutes.","Add remaining 90 g water, remaining 300 g flour, 10 g remaining sugar and salt then knead <nobr>4 min\/<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer dough to prepared bowl, cover with cling film and leave in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 2-3 hours). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place water and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl then insert simmering basket and weigh in quinoa. Cook <nobr>20 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, place linseeds and 3 Tbsp water in a small bowl and stir. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer quinoa to a bowl to cool. Empty mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Burger","content":["Place oil, shallots, garlic, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>7 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Sauté <nobr>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add beans, breadcrumbs, nuts, tomato purée, cumin, paprika, reserved linseed and water, reserved quinoa and ½ tsp salt then mix <nobr>20 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl, cover with cling film then refrigerate.","When dough has doubled in size, line 2 baking trays with baking paper. Tip dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead gently. Divide dough into 4 portions and shape into rolls. Arrange rolls on 1 prepared baking tray, cover with oiled cling film and allow to rise for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, using a pastry ring, form 4 burgers (Ø 10 cm) with reserved burger mixture then place in fridge. Towards end of rising time, preheat oven to 180°C.","Brush tops of risen rolls with oil and sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake for 15-20 minutes (180°C) until cooked and tops of rolls are golden brown.","Remove rolls from oven and place on a wire rack to cool.","Transfer burgers to second baking tray and bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until a 'crust' has formed on the burgers. Remove tray from oven and place peppers (if using) over burgers then cook for a further 2-3 minutes (180°C)."]},{"title":"To Serve","content":["Slice buns in half, then place burgers inside. Top with tomato ketchup, lettuce, sliced tomatoes, sliced avocado and a few rings of red onion."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Bread","content":["15 g granulated sugar","350 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","140 g water","5 g fresh yeast","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp oil, for greasing"]},{"title":"Burger","content":["1200 g water, plus 3 Tbsp","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","100 g quinoa","1 Tbsp linseeds (flaxseeds)","30 g extra virgin olive oil","30 g shallots","1 garlic clove","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","200 g black beans, tinned, drained and rinsed","10 g breadcrumbs","35 g halved walnuts","20 g tomato purée","2 tsp ground cumin","2 tsp smoked paprika, sweet"]},{"title":"To Serve","content":["1 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil","2 - 3 tsp poppy seeds","4 slices red pepper, preserved              (optional)","4 Tbsp ketchup","4 - 6 curly endive, wash and dried","8 - 12 slices tomatoes","1 avocado, peeled and sliced, or to taste (optional)","1 red onion, sliced in rings, or to taste (optional)"]}],"id":"r121147","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-RnZrN7e7JLs\/XZVPTLx1KLI\/AAAAAAAAc3I\/msR1oQXM-vY0tZQvxfCcCvLJ5GZfMstNACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4KEsNv7TCz-dFBBr.png","title":"Vegan Burger","publishedAt":"2016-10-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21.7 g","fat":"29.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"112 g","calories":"3222 kJ \/ 770 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, cling film, pastry cutter, 2 baking trays and baking paper, pastry brush, wire rack, baking tray and paper, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The burgers can be seared in a hot frying pan if desired."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","4h 55m","4 portions"]}